he PRD requirement.\n2. `matching.service.ts` line 498 emits `match:created` eve
nt AFTER transaction, which is good. `ImService.handleMatchCreated` listens to i
t and creates system message. This follows the recommended pattern.\n3. `im.serv
ice.ts` lines 442-454 uses native SQL with `?` placeholders - this is correct pe
r nestjs.md.\n4. `im.gateway.ts` line 23 has `@UsePipes(new ValidationPipe(...))
